    "ideation": "The animation interprets the man with a probing cane not just as a literal figure, but as an exercise in sensory exploration. The eyes are not focused on a visual point; instead, they are closed, with eyelids lowered to represent the shift from sight to other senses. The gaze moves rhythmically, but disconnected from eye scale, mimicking the sweeping motion of a cane across the floor. The mouth becomes the tactile 'echo' of the cane's tap: a gentle, rhythmic pulse that hits a high-frequency buzz at the moment of contact with an obstacle. The color palette uses deep, introspective indigos and soft greys to convey a world of sound, texture, and internal mapping.",
